	<clause id="duration-general" obligation="normative"><title>Explicit forms</title><clause id="value-restriction" obligation="normative"><title>Value prefixing</title><p id="_921fc30c-f227-416b-8eba-68f9d85c5205">Prefixing of the value with one or more “`0`”s (the number zero) to the
	integer [i] is allowed in the explicit forms of time scale components.</p>
	<example id="_a7b99c57-41bf-4ad2-a9dc-013f75c53488">
	<p id="_0993b8c7-ec1a-4f9f-a253-14d74955912d">‘1M’, ‘01M’, and ‘0001M’ all describe the calendar month January.</p>
