	<clause id="_prerequisite_mechanisms" obligation="normative"><title>Prerequisite mechanisms</title><clause id="_carry_over_of_overflow_in_time_scale_components" obligation="normative"><title>Carry-over of overflow in time scale components</title><p id="_a16436c9-ace3-4531-b8fd-3704b6abddc2">An “overflow” of a date and time expression is defined as assigning a
	value exceeding the maximum value accepted by the time scale component.</p>
	<example id="_02f69a93-5bf1-4b77-bd49-b2c700d3dfe3">
	<p id="_c452fea6-f1ef-4172-8252-4a8e489eca4e">An increase of <tt>P1M</tt> (duration) to <tt>2018Y12M</tt> (date) will result in the expression
	<tt>2018Y13M</tt>, where the month component is overflowed with value <tt>13</tt>.</p>


